  <static seed="593" source="PCC-ORCCA-ed3/BasicAlgebra/QuadraticApplications/FlyingObjectApp40.pg">
    <statement><p>A submarine is traveling in the sea. Its depth, in meters, can be modeled by <m>d={-1.8t^{2}+28.8t-110.2}</m>, where <m>t</m> stands for time in seconds. The submarine <ul form="popup" name="AnSwEr0001"><li>
<p>?</p>
</li><li>
<p>will</p>
</li><li>
<p>will not</p>
</li></ul> hit the sea surface along this route.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\text{will}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To determine whether the submarine will surface, we substitute <m>d(t)=0</m> into <m>d(t)={-1.8t^{2}+28.8t-110.2}</m>, and solve the equation by the Quadratic Formula:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{
        \begin{aligned}
            t \amp  = \frac{-b\pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}\\
              \amp  = \frac{-({28.8})\pm\sqrt{({28.8})^2-4(-1.8)({-110.2})}}{2(-1.8)}\\
                   \amp  = \frac{{-28.8}\pm\sqrt{{829.44}-{793.44}}}{-3.6}\\
                   \amp  = \frac{{-28.8}\pm\sqrt{{36}}}{-3.6}\\
                  \amp \approx \frac{-28.8\pm 6}{-3.6} \\\amp \approx \frac{-28.8+6}{-3.6}\text{ or }\frac{-28.8-6}{-3.6} \\\amp \approx 6.33\text{ or }9.67
        \end{aligned}
     }</m></p>
<p>The submarine will surface approximately `6.33` seconds later.</p>
</solution>
